Cel:+507 6301-0401 (WhatsApp)
Email: xrodriguez@busportgroup.com
Movement within Panama is restricted, but for those with tickets, travel to the airport for repatriation is a valid exemption.
The British Embassy can facilitate a safe passage letter in Spanish and English for the driver for use at checkpoints to and from the airport. Email us your flight confirmation along with the following details:
the driver’s full name
identification number (cedula)
licence plate number
make and model of the vehicle
names of British nationals traveling with you
If you are having difficulty booking transportation, we may be able to assist.
If you are travelling outside the Panama City, we encourage you arrive in Panama City the day prior to the flight, to prevent any last minute delays. See a list of hotels in Panama City that you may find helpful.
Arrival in France
Onward travel from Paris is your responsibility and must be booked in advance. Flights continue to operate between Paris and other European cities, but availability may be reduced. There are flights running from Paris to London, Manchester, Edinburgh and Dublin. Tickets can be booked here.
All travellers must complete an international travel authorisation on the same day of travel to France.
Travellers who have to leave Paris CDG Airport to continue their journey must also complete an authorisation for movement on French territory.
Authorisation forms will also be available at the airport on the day of the flight.
See FCO Travel Advice relating to France for further advice.
Future travel options
This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
Your journey home
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air.
When you arrive back in the UK, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy on +507 297-6550 or through the recommended consular contacts.
The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available. To get the latest information, sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
If you cannot leave Panama
If you cannot leave Panama at this time, you should email your details to BEPanama.CV@fco.gov.uk, so we can alert you when options become available.
See also staying in Panama during coronavirus.
